      {
        "content": "Social media's current design prioritizes engagement over user well-being, often leading to harmful mental health effects such as anxiety, depression, and loneliness. Algorithms amplify negative content and create echo chambers, exacerbating stress and polarization. The endless scroll and notification systems are engineered to be addictive, disrupting sleep patterns and reducing real-life social interactions. Implementing reforms, such as mental health-conscious algorithms and features that promote digital well-being, can mitigate these issues. By prioritizing user mental health, social media can transform into a tool that enhances, rather than harms, psychological well-being.",
